     58          *       (OS_Error)
     59          *
     60          **********************************************************************
     61          
     62           Run-time error reaction
     63          
     64           When this happens, a fatal error has occurred and the kernel
     65           can not continue. In Linux, the equivalent would be a
     66           "kernel panic"
     67          
     68           This routine can be modified to suit your needs ...
     69           E.g. a red LED could light up. When using an
     70           emulator, you may set a breakpoint here.
     71           In the release builds of the library (R), this routine is not required
     72           (as no checks are performed).
     73           In the stack check builds (S/SP), only error 120 may occur.
     74           In the debug builds(D/DP), all of the listed errors may occur.
     75          
     76           The following are the current errorcodes:
     77           (Please refer to the documentation for more info)
     78          
     79          *** Port 100..119 ********************************
     80          OS_ERR_ISR_INDEX                      (100 = 0x64)
     81          OS_ERR_ISR_VECTOR                     (101 = 0x65)
     82          OS_ERR_ISR_PRIO                       (102 = 0x66)
     83          OS_ERR_WRONG_STACK                    (103 = 0x67)
     84          OS_ERR_ISR_NO_HANDLER                 (104 = 0x68)  *** No interrupt handler was defined for this interrupt
     85          OS_ERR_TLS_INIT                       (105 = 0x69)  *** OS_TLS_Init() called multiple times from one task
     86          OS_ERR_MB_BUFFER_SIZE                 (106 = 0x6A)  *** For 16bit CPUs, the maximum buffer size for a mailbox (64KB) exceeded
     87          
     88          *** OS generic ***********************************
     89          
     90          OS_ERR_EXTEND_CONTEXT                 (116 = 0x74)  *** OS_ExtendTaskContext called multiple times from one task
     91          OS_ERR_TIMESLICE                      (117 = 0x75)  *** A timeslice value of 0 (illegal) was set.
     92          OS_ERR_INTERNAL                       (118 = 0x76)  *** OS_ChangeTask called without RegionCnt set (or other internal error)
     93          OS_ERR_IDLE_RETURNS                   (119 = 0x77)  *** Idle loop should not return
     94          
     95          *** Stack overflow ******************************
     96          OS_ERR_STACK                          (120 = 0x78)  *** Stack overflow or invalid stack
     97          
     98          *** Counting semaphore overflow ******************
     99          OS_ERR_CSEMA_OVERFLOW                 (121 = 0x79)
    100          
